Description: rename ZLE's getline() widget to zlegetline()
 The ZLE "get-line" widget is a C function literally named getline(), and its
 generated prototype conflicts with the POSIX getline() musl declares in
 <stdio.h> ("conflicting types for 'getline'"). A -Dgetline=... macro cannot fix
 this, because it would rename musl's declaration too. Rename the widget itself,
 in the definition and in Src/Zle/iwidgets.list; the .epro prototype is
 regenerated from the .c, so it needs no edit.
Origin: vendor, shell-versions
Forwarded: not-needed

--- Src/Zle/zle_hist.c
+++ Src/Zle/zle_hist.c
@@ -558,7 +558,7 @@
 
 /**/
 int
-getline(char **args)
+zlegetline(char **args)
 {
     char *s = (char *)getlinknode(bufstack);
 
--- Src/Zle/iwidgets.list
+++ Src/Zle/iwidgets.list
@@ -56,7 +56,7 @@
 "expand-word", expandword, 0
 "forward-char", forwardchar, 0
 "forward-word", forwardword, 0
-"get-line", getline, 0
+"get-line", zlegetline, 0
 "gosmacs-transpose-chars", gosmacstransposechars, 0
 "history-beginning-search-backward", historybeginningsearchbackward, 0
 "history-beginning-search-forward", historybeginningsearchforward, 0
